# Method of Cylindrical Shells

## Vertical Axis of Revolution

https://calcworkshop.com/wp-content/uploads/shell-method-around-y-axis.png
![../60-Meta-Attachments/e7236cb30a702159c5d45b3841fd71e4.png](data:image/png;base64,)

$$

V=2\pi \int ^{b}_{a} x f(x) dx


$$

## Horizontal Axis of Revolution

![[w/-3-Powerful-Examples!|How To Use The Shell Method? (w/ 3 Powerful Examples!]]]])

$$

V=2\pi \int ^{b}_{a} y f(y) dy


$$
